      <span class="faq-q-text">Stop renting traffic. Start owning it. Stacc publishes 30 SEO articles per month for $99. Build a traffic asset that compounds every month. Start for $1 → Where PPC Outperforms SEO PPC wins in 4 specific scenarios. These advantages matter most for speed-dependent businesses. Immediate Traffic PPC delivers clicks the same day you launch. SEO takes 4 to 12 months to produce meaningful results. If you need leads this week, PPC is the only option. New businesses, product launches, seasonal promotions, and time-sensitive campaigns all require immediate visibility that SEO cannot provide. Precise Audience Targeting PPC allows you to target by: - Exact keywords and match types - Geographic location (down to ZIP code) - Device type (mobile, desktop) - Time of day and day of week - Demographics (age, household income) - Remarketing audiences (people who visited your site before) SEO targets keywords. PPC targets people. That targeting precision makes PPC valuable for testing and for reaching specific audience segments. Keyword Testing and Validation PPC provides immediate data on which keywords convert. Before investing 6 months of SEO effort into a keyword, run a PPC campaign for 2 weeks. If the keyword converts profitably via PPC, it will likely convert even better via organic search. This test-first approach prevents wasting SEO resources on keywords that attract traffic but do not generate revenue. Use PPC data to inform your keyword research and content strategy. Scalable Budget Control PPC gives you complete control over spending. Set a daily budget of $50 or $5,000. Pause campaigns instantly. Increase spend during peak seasons and reduce during slow periods. SEO budgets are less flexible. You cannot scale organic traffic up or down on a weekly basis. The investment is front-loaded and the returns are delayed. PPC matches the cash flow patterns of seasonal and variable-revenue businesses. SERP Domination Running PPC and SEO simultaneously lets you own multiple positions on the same results page. A business ranking organically in position 1 and showing a paid ad above it captures significantly more total clicks than either channel alone. Semrush data shows that combined organic + paid presence increases total click-through by 25% compared to organic alone. Remarketing Power PPC enables remarketing to people who visited your site but did not convert. An organic visitor reads your blog post and leaves. A PPC remarketing ad follows them across the web, bringing them back when they are ready to act. This capability turns organic traffic into a PPC asset. SEO attracts the initial visit. PPC remarketing closes the loop. No other channel combination works this efficiently for recapturing abandoned visitors. The Budget Allocation Framework The standard advice is "do both." That is unhelpful when your budget is $2,000 per month. Here is a staged approach based on business maturity and budget. Stage 1: New Business (Months 0-3) Budget split: 80% PPC / 20% SEO</span>
