o marginal cost. A business spending $2,000 per month on PPC for 24 months spends $48,000 total and owns nothing at the end. A business investing $2,000 per month in SEO for 24 months spends $48,000 total and owns a content library generating thousands of monthly visits for free. The break-even point varies by industry. Most businesses reach SEO break-even (where cumulative organic value exceeds cumulative spend) between months 8 and 14. After break-even, every additional month of organic traffic is pure profit. This math explains why 49% of marketers rank organic search as their most profitable channel. It also explains why experienced businesses shift their budget toward SEO over time while maintaining a smaller PPC allocation for speed and testing. Rank everywhere. Do nothing. Blog SEO, Local SEO, and Social on autopilot. Stacc starts at $99/mo with a $1 trial. Start for $1 → FAQ Is SEO cheaper than PPC?</span>
