    <div class="faq-a" id="what-is-the-average-roi-of-seo-vs-ppc"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>SEO delivers a median ROI of approximately 748% over 2 to 3 years, with some sectors exceeding 1,000%. PPC delivers approximately 200% ROI (roughly $2 per $1 spent). The difference grows over time because SEO costs plateau while traffic compounds. PPC costs grow linearly with traffic.</p></div></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>The SEO vs PPC decision is not either-or. It is a sequencing question. Use PPC for speed when you need it. Invest in SEO for the long-term asset. The businesses outperforming their competitors in 2026 figured out the right ratio at the right time. Start with the data, allocate based on your stage, and shift toward organic as it compounds.</p>
